## 🧩 Component Structure

**Astro Component Structure in /components/**
```
component-name/
├── component-name.astro
└── index.ts
```

**Component index.ts Example:**
```ts
// components/component-name/index.ts
export { default } from './component-name.astro';
```

---

## 🎯 Core Principles

### Component Structure Order
1. **Frontmatter section (`---`)**: All JavaScript/TypeScript logic
2. **Template section**: HTML/JSX markup
3. **Style section**: Scoped CSS (optional)

### Frontmatter Best Practices
- **Always use TypeScript**: Add type annotations for props
- **Keep frontmatter pure**: No side effects, only data preparation
- **Use async/await**: For data fetching in frontmatter
- **Props interface**: Always define `ComponentNameProps` interface

```astro
---
interface PageProps {
  title: string;
  description?: string;
}

const { title, description = 'Default description' }: PageProps = Astro.props;
---
```

---

## 🔌 Svelte Component Integration

### Client Directives
Use appropriate client directives for Svelte components:

```astro
---
import SvelteComponent from '../features/feature/components/component.svelte';
---

<!-- Load immediately (default) -->
<SvelteComponent client:load />

<!-- Load when visible (lazy) -->
<SvelteComponent client:visible />

<!-- Load on idle (performance) -->
<SvelteComponent client:idle />

<!-- Load on media query -->
<SvelteComponent client:media="(max-width: 768px)" />

<!-- Only hydrate, no JS until interaction -->
<SvelteComponent client:only="svelte" />
```

### When to Use Each Directive
- **`client:load`**: Critical interactive components (headers, forms)
- **`client:visible`**: Below-the-fold content (lazy loading)
- **`client:idle`**: Non-critical features (analytics, widgets)
- **`client:only`**: Client-only components (avoid SSR)

