## 🧩 Feature Integration Pattern

### Astro Wrapper for Svelte Features
```astro
---
// src/features/footer/containers/footer-astro.astro
import Footer from '../components/footer.svelte';
import { defineFooterColumns } from '../services.svelte';

const columns = defineFooterColumns();
---

<Footer columns={columns} client:load />
```

### Page Using Features
```astro
---
// src/pages/index.astro
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { FooterAstro } from '../features/footer';
---

<Layout>
  <main>
    <!-- Page content -->
  </main>
  <FooterAstro client:load />
</Layout>
```

---

## 🚫 Anti-Patterns

### ❌ Don't Use
- **Inline styles** (use Tailwind or scoped styles)
- **Global `<style>` without scoping** (use `:global()` or separate CSS file)
- **`client:load` everywhere** (use appropriate directive)
- **Props without TypeScript interfaces**
- **Side effects in frontmatter** (only data preparation)
- **Direct DOM manipulation** (use Svelte components for interactivity)

### ✅ Do Use
- **TypeScript interfaces for props**
- **TailwindCSS for styling**
- **Appropriate client directives**
- **Feature-based organization**
- **Layout components for structure**
- **Scoped styles when needed**

---

## 📝 Code Style

### Naming Conventions
- **Files**: `kebab-case.astro` (e.g., `footer-wrapper.astro`)
- **Components**: `PascalCase` in imports (e.g., `FooterWrapper`)
- **Props interfaces**: `ComponentNameProps` (e.g., `FooterWrapperProps`)

### Import Order
1. Astro imports (`astro:assets`, `astro:content`)
2. Layout imports
3. Feature component imports
4. Utility/type imports
5. Style imports

### Comments
- Start file with path comment: `// apps/seo/ui/src/components/component-name.astro`
- Comment purpose, not effect
- Use JSDoc for complex functions

---

## 🔍 TypeScript Integration

### Type Safety
- Always define prop interfaces
- Use TypeScript in frontmatter
- Leverage Astro's built-in types

```astro
---
import type { AstroGlobal } from 'astro';

interface PageProps {
  title: string;
}

const { title }: PageProps = Astro.props;
const url: string = Astro.url.pathname;
---
```

### Type Definitions
- Extend `app.d.ts` for custom types
- Use Astro's type helpers when available
- Import types from feature modules

